 wanted some second opinions.  It's a little sloppy, but still reigns as the best Anime style art that I've colored <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> drawn.  Tell me what you think, thanks. (I know this is a colorists board, but feel free to give tips on drawing as well). Later.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/fl5/liquidartstudios/images/Ryu2_-Fine-_copy.jpg">www.angelfire.com/fl5/liq...-_copy.jpg</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
(I hope that link works..)<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darkreaver66>darkreaver66</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>double wookie</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/18/03 8:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9847.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> hmmm it is indeed a little sloppy...do you plan on fixing that up?...<br>
<br>
I find it strange that you used cel shading in the face, but used more of an airbrushed effect in the hair...I would suggest making them more consistent...cel shading in the hair would make it cleaner.In any case, I feel that the white highlights should be a lot harder and better defined.<br>
<br>
The shadows and highlights in the hair are too numerous and evenly spaced....for one thing, you dont get multiple centers of highlight if the hair merely follows the curve of the head (i.e. the hair isnt wavy, or flowing)...there should be only one strong highlight, from where the lightsource hits the hair the most.<br>
<br>
shading is a little inconsistent...for example, you missed some cast shadow from one of the strands of hair on our right side....<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sevenwingangel>Seven Wing Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/18/03 8:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9847.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> The cel shading on the body is pretty good, but like DarkReaver said the hair could use some work.   The hair itself is kind of blocky, but u could be going for the blocky look.  But if your going to make it so blocky you might not want to have all those smaller strands of hair near the ears and etc.   Also, the highlights on the hair should be somewhat consitant, so think of it kind of like a band of highlight circumscribed around the hair, but adjusting it a little depending on how much the hair protrudes and etc.   Also, the iridescent iris is kinda wierd, but nice job, the style is pretty good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=giorrie>giorrie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/18/03 9:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9847.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> it kinda looks like he's in a plastic wrap, and the shading on his face shouldn't be that red <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eskiers@polykarbonbbs>eskiers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/18/03 10:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9847.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> looks good. the cell shading on the face is really cool.<br>
the hair i think is somthing you need to work on more. make it shaded like the face. and cleaner lines on it maybe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xenodude>Xenodude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/20/03 1:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9847.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Wow, I've never been to a board where I've gotten this much feedback, thanks.  I'll take everything you've said into consideration.  I guess I'll re-color the pic keeping those things in mind and see how the second version comes out.  Thanks; later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xenodude>Xenodude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/20/03 3:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9847.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Alright, I redid the picture taking in some of the things you said.  I still kept the same style for the hair, but it's a little less random.  Everything seems to have a general toned down feeling.  However, I'm still having trouble conveying the sense of heat and it still lacks whatever it is that makes things look professional.  Here's the second version: <br>
<br>
